00:23:49.553 --> 00:23:52.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and suddenly the coldness

419
00:23:52.180 --> 00:23:55.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of being alone in the crib.

420
00:23:57.102 --> 00:23:59.187 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a terrible deprivation.

421
00:24:03.316 --> 00:24:07.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kellman] <i>I remember being told</i>
<i>by my mother when I was a baby</i>

422
00:24:07.279 --> 00:24:09.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that I would slam my head
against the wall.

423
00:24:10.407 --> 00:24:12.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would... I would basically
knock myself out.

424
00:24:12.742 --> 00:24:16.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My mother said I would bang my head
on the inside of the crib.

425
00:24:19.332 --> 00:24:22.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I would hold my breath
until I passed out.

426
00:24:24.337 --> 00:24:26.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I believe it was absolutely...

427
00:24:27.132 --> 00:24:28.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Separation anxiety.</i>

428
00:24:33.430 --> 00:24:36.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All of us had been adopted
from Louise Wise Services.

429
00:24:36.975 --> 00:24:38.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mike Wallace] <i>Louise Wise Services,</i>

430
00:24:39.019 --> 00:24:43.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the New York institution</i>
<i>founded back in 1916,</i>

431
00:24:43.273 --> 00:24:45.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>overseen by a board of directors</i>

432
00:24:45.358 --> 00:24:49.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>drawn from New York City's social,</i>
<i>financial, and political elite.</i>

433
00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:55.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kellman] <i>They were the preeminent</i>
<i>adoption agency on the East Coast</i>

434
00:24:55.869 --> 00:24:58.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for Jewish babies, in particular.

435
00:24:58.955 --> 00:25:01.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was the place to go.

436
00:25:01.458 --> 00:25:05.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What we have felt at Louise Wise Services,

437
00:25:05.712 --> 00:25:09.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
where I have been active
for a great long time,

438
00:25:09.382 --> 00:25:13.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
is that adoptive parents should be told

439
00:25:13.345 --> 00:25:17.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as much about the background of a child
as is reasonable.

440
00:25:18.016 --> 00:25:20.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our parents, they...
They wanted answers.

441
00:25:20.852 --> 00:25:21.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They were angry.

442
00:25:21.937 --> 00:25:23.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And they arranged a meeting,

443
00:25:23.438 --> 00:25:24.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they, uh, uh...

444
00:25:25.023 --> 00:25:28.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Six of them went
into Louise Wise Agency...

445
00:25:29.819 --> 00:25:31.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>to try to get some answers</i>

446
00:25:31.279 --> 00:25:33.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>in terms of piecing together</i>
<i>what happened.</i>

447
00:25:38.161 --> 00:25:40.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[thunder rumbling]

448
00:25:45.460 --> 00:25:50.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Alice] <i>There was a meeting</i>
<i>with the top brass at the agency.</i>

449
00:25:51.633 --> 00:25:53.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And they were asked,</i>

450
00:25:53.635 --> 00:25:56.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"Is it true that you separated
these boys at birth?"

451
00:26:03.186 --> 00:26:05.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And they said, "Yes, we did."</i>

452
00:26:08.942 --> 00:26:10.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Why?

453
00:26:12.362 --> 00:26:14.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How could you not tell us?

454
00:26:14.781 --> 00:26:16.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you do?

455
00:26:17.575 --> 00:26:19.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why, and how could you?"

456
00:26:22.122 --> 00:26:23.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Alice] <i>They said the reason</i>

457
00:26:23.957 --> 00:26:28.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>was because it was hard</i>
<i>to place three children in one home.</i>

458
00:26:30.380 --> 00:26:31.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Shafran] <i>The parents had been told</i>

459
00:26:32.048 --> 00:26:35.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that it was in our best interests
that we'd been split up.

460
00:26:35.677 --> 00:26:40.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That not every parent
would welcome triplets

461
00:26:40.098 --> 00:26:44.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and that triplets
would be difficult to place.

462
00:26:44.936 --> 00:26:46.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which...

463
00:26:47.564 --> 00:26:50.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think, at that moment,
my father blew his stack

464
00:26:50.775 --> 00:26:52.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and just said,
"We would've taken all three."

465
00:26:53.820 --> 00:26:55.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's no question.

466
00:26:55.447 --> 00:26:56.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And he was furious.

467
00:26:58.408 --> 00:27:01.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs] Well, the meeting came to an end.

468
00:27:03.913 --> 00:27:07.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Shafran] <i>They all left.</i>
<i>They felt like they had gotten nothing.</i>

469
00:27:08.752 --> 00:27:11.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And my father realized that
he had left his umbrella in there.

470
00:27:16.468 --> 00:27:19.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And he went back to get the umbrella.

471
00:27:23.016 --> 00:27:25.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And he walked into the room</i>

472
00:27:25.935 --> 00:27:29.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to see them breaking open</i>
<i>a bottle of champagne...</i>

473
00:27:32.692 --> 00:27:36.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And toasting each other</i>
<i>as if they had dodged a bullet.</i>

474
00:27:39.240 --> 00:27:41.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They looked like they'd just...

475
00:27:41.951 --> 00:27:44.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Just missed, uh,

476
00:27:45.580 --> 00:27:49.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
getting hurt or killed or what have you.

477
00:27:49.376 --> 00:27:51.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was a, uh...

478
00:27:51.795 --> 00:27:54.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was memorable.

479
00:27:55.965 --> 00:27:58.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kellman] <i>All of our parents came away</i>
<i>from that meeting angry.</i>

480
00:28:04.974 --> 00:28:08.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Shafran] <i>The parents went to some</i>
<i>pretty prestigious New York law firms</i>

481
00:28:08.103 --> 00:28:12.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and, initially, they were met
with a lot of enthusiasm.

482
00:28:12.440 --> 00:28:16.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And, um, invariably,
within a short period of time,

483
00:28:16.194 --> 00:28:19.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
were told there's a conflict

484
00:28:19.239 --> 00:28:21.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they could not take the case.

485
00:28:21.866 --> 00:28:25.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They said, "We have a number of associates

486
00:28:25.370 --> 00:28:28.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who are trying to adopt
through Louise Wise,

487
00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:31.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and we don't want to ruin their chances."

488
00:28:33.002 --> 00:28:35.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So that lawsuit was out.

489
00:28:41.636 --> 00:28:45.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kellman] <i>We were too happy</i>
<i>being together to be that angry.</i>

490
00:28:45.223 --> 00:28:46.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We didn't understand it,

491
00:28:46.766 --> 00:28:49.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and to a degree, we almost didn't care.

492
00:28:52.856 --> 00:28:54.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Our heads were in the clouds.</i>

493
00:28:54.858 --> 00:28:56.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We knew our parents were pissed off,</i>

494
00:28:56.776 --> 00:28:59.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but it was almost like, well,</i>
<i>that's our parents' thing to do</i>

495
00:29:00.071 --> 00:29:02.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
while we were out partying.

496
00:29:05.076 --> 00:29:07.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Shafran] <i>This was New York in 1980.</i>

497
00:29:09.164 --> 00:29:10.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Drugs were different.
People were different.

498
00:29:10.957 --> 00:29:12.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sex was different. Music was different.

499
00:29:12.917 --> 00:29:14.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[exhales] We just...

500
00:29:14.502 --> 00:29:16.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We just took advantage
of all those things.

501
00:29:16.671 --> 00:29:18.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sex, drugs, rock and roll.

502
00:29:18.923 --> 00:29:20.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

503
00:29:23.887 --> 00:29:26.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They were running amok
in New York, I'll say.

504
00:29:28.558 --> 00:29:30.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Cervone] <i>Studio 54 was cooking.</i>

505
00:29:31.186 --> 00:29:34.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Limelight. Copacabana.
They were hitting them all.

506
00:29:36.274 --> 00:29:38.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kellman] <i>New York loved us.</i>
<i>New York loved us.</i>

507
00:29:41.946 --> 00:29:44.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All the newspapers
were following the boys around,

508
00:29:44.657 --> 00:29:45.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no matter where we went.

509
00:29:47.786 --> 00:29:50.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kellman] <i>I remember</i>
<i>one morning walking in</i>

510
00:29:50.622 --> 00:29:53.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and my mother throwing the <i>New York Post</i>

511
00:29:54.709 --> 00:29:57.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
at me, at the kitchen table, saying,

512
00:29:57.253 --> 00:30:00.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"I gotta look at the paper to find out
where you were last night?" [laughs]

513
00:30:03.468 --> 00:30:06.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Alice] <i>The boys thought</i>
<i>they were going to be stars,</i>

514
00:30:06.554 --> 00:30:10.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and actually they did star
in one movie. [laughs]

515
00:30:11.434 --> 00:30:14.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kellman] <i>Walking down the street,</i>
<i>all of a sudden we hear,</i>

516
00:30:14.813 --> 00:30:17.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Guys! Guys! You're the guys!

517
00:30:17.982 --> 00:30:20.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Could you please be in my movie?
Please be in my movie."

518
00:30:26.491 --> 00:30:29.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We didn't know who she was,
and she was... She was Madonna.

519
00:30:30.703 --> 00:30:33.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They stood on the side and ogled her.

520
00:30:33.623 --> 00:30:37.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Pretty soon we got an apartment together,
the triplets' apartment.

521
00:30:38.753 --> 00:30:41.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The triplets' apartment, hmm!

522
00:30:41.256 --> 00:30:43.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's like if you had

523
00:30:43.383 --> 00:30:46.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the most bachelor apartment times three.

524
00:30:47.011 --> 00:30:48.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The liquor store used
to deliver the liquor.

525
00:30:51.683 --> 00:30:54.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At one point, Eddy had appendicitis.

526
00:30:55.979 --> 00:30:57.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He had no insurance.

527
00:30:57.856 --> 00:31:00.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And so he checked
into the hospital as Bobby

528
00:31:01.526 --> 00:31:03.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and had his appendix taken out, as Bobby.</i>

529
00:31:03.653 --> 00:31:06.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope to this day,
Bobby's appendix stays pretty healthy.

530
00:31:08.533 --> 00:31:10.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Shafran] <i>Between working together,</i>
<i>playing together,</i>

531
00:31:10.743 --> 00:31:14.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>going out together,</i>
<i>going on dates together, living together,</i>

532
00:31:14.622 --> 00:31:17.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>from the time we met till...</i>

533
00:31:18.918 --> 00:31:21.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, till later, there was nothing,

534
00:31:21.170 --> 00:31:23.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
nothing that could keep us apart.

535
00:31:23.798 --> 00:31:26.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Ilene Shafran]<i> I feel like I was</i>
<i>the first serious girlfriend.</i>

536
00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:31.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Initially,</i>
<i>I couldn't really tell them apart,</i>

537
00:31:31.848 --> 00:31:33.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and I would bump into them,</i>

538
00:31:33.391 --> 00:31:37.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
and I wasn't quite sure which one
I was going out with, so...

539
00:31:38.479 --> 00:31:41.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Bob has this very raw,</i>

540
00:31:41.441 --> 00:31:43.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>natural type of intelligence</i>

541
00:31:44.152 --> 00:31:45.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that I think I was attracted to.

542
00:31:46.321 --> 00:31:49.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I always thought David was, um...

543
00:31:50.408 --> 00:31:52.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
The best, right, of the three of them.

544
00:31:52.994 --> 00:31:54.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've said it before.

545
00:31:54.662 --> 00:31:56.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You know, "I got the pick of the litter."

546
00:31:58.416 --> 00:32:02.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Without a doubt,
Eddy was the, um, handsomest

547
00:32:02.378 --> 00:32:05.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
of all the three triplets, yeah.

548
00:32:05.715 --> 00:32:07.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Of course, I'm partial,

549
00:32:07.550 --> 00:32:10.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
but, you know, I adored him.

550
00:32:12.430 --> 00:32:14.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>When I met him,</i>

551
00:32:14.474 --> 00:32:16.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>he was the last holdout.</i>

552
00:32:17.393 --> 00:32:19.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The Casanova of the three.</i>

553
00:32:22.148 --> 00:32:25.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I said, "Oh, boy,
this guy's a real bachelor, like, player."

554
00:32:28.196 --> 00:32:31.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But he was so warm in his smile,</i>

555
00:32:31.366 --> 00:32:35.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and he had wonderful,</i>
<i>beautiful hands, soft hands.</i>

556
00:32:35.286 --> 00:32:37.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And when I shook his hand,
I mean, I just...

557
00:32:37.580 --> 00:32:39.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know, I just fell in love with him.

558
00:32:43.044 --> 00:32:46.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I'm from a big, colorful</i>
